    %h2 /accounts
    
    %p
      User accounts. Readonly.
    
    %h3 GET on /accounts/<em>:account_id</em>, /accounts/current
    
    :markdown
      Download the information of current account.
      
      <em>:account_id</em> is either an integer which specifies an ID of account, or <code>current</code>.
      If <code>current</code> is given in request, the client's authenticated account will be in the response.
    
    .row
      .span8
        %h4 Response
        %pre
          = preserve do
            :escaped
              {
                "account": $account,
                "timestamp": "2011-11-02T09:11:34Z",
              }
      .span8
        %h4 Fields
        %dl
          %dt account
          %dd The account.
          %dt timestamp
          %dd The time in ubiregi.com server.

    %h3 Note

    :markdown
      Accesses to /accounts/ do not expire.
      
      Even if your account is expired, it returns the account's information.
      
      It is allowed to access child accounts.
      If you access your child accounts, you will receive the information of the account.
      In other case, your request will result in 404 (not found) error.
    
    %h2 /accounts/<em>:account_id</em>/cashiers
    
    :markdown
      Collection of cashiers defined in the user's account.
    
    %h3 POST on /accounts/<em>:account_id</em>/cashiers

    :markdown
      Update the cashiers of an account specified by *:account_id*.
      The child account's cashiers can be updated by parents.
    
    .row
      .span8
        %h4 Request
        %pre
          = preserve do
            :escaped
              {
                "cashiers": [
                  {
                    "name": "New cashier",
                    "enabled":true,
                    "icon":$base64Encoded,
                  },
                  {
                    "id": 1,
                    "name": "Updating an existing cashier",
                    "enabled": false,
                  }
                ]
              }
      .span8
        %h4 Fields
        
        %dl
          %dt id
          %dd
            ID of cashier object.
            If unspecified, create a new cashier object.
            If specified, update an existing cashier object.
          %dt name
          %dt enabled
          %dt icon
          %dd
            Base64 encoded data of icon.
            If unspecified, the icon is not updated.
            If specified with <code>null</code>, the icon will be removed.

    .row
      .span8
        %h4 Response
        %pre
          = preserve do
            :escaped
              {
                "timestamp": "2011-11-02T09:11:12Z",
                "cashiers" : $cashiers
              }
      .span8
        %p
          The order of the cashier objects are preserved.
          
        %p
          The update/creation is transactional.
          There are only two cases; everything processed successfully, or nothing changed since an error found.
          

